	"metadata": {
		"title": "dotnet: kestrel: closing an HTTP/3 stream can cause a race condition and lead to remote code execution (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-38229",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-38229",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in dotnet. When closing an HTTP/3 stream while application code is writing to the response body, a race condition can cause a use-after-free. \n            STATEMENT: .NET 8.0 (dotnet8.0) was released for RHEL 8 starting with RHEL 8.9. Therefore, this .NET version is not affected in RHEL 8.8 and previous versions.\n\n.NET 8.0 (dotnet8.0) was released for RHEL 9 starting with RHEL 9.3. Therefore, this .NET version is not affected in RHEL 9.2 and previous versions.\n            MITIGATION: Red Hat has investigated whether a possible mitigation exists for this issue, and has not been able to identify a practical example. Please update the affected package as soon as possible.",
